From these test results it could be concluded that for full circle trenches surrounding the source of vibration at a distance of one wave length or less, the scaled depth of the trench must be about
0.6 for the trench to be effective . For full circle trenches the screened zone included an area of the half space outside of the trench extending to a radius of at least 10 wave lengths. Data was not obtained beyond 10 wave lengths due to the site size and the vibration exciter power capabilities.
